1
00:02:45,760 --> 00:02:47,900
Who exactly am I?

2
00:04:04,011 --> 00:04:06,100
I saw him at Mr. Jit's house.

3
00:04:11,041 --> 00:04:14,582
Jit, you brought him here?

4
00:04:14,582 --> 00:04:16,283
I mean...

5
00:04:21,280 --> 00:04:22,981
It's not my dad.

6
00:04:24,499 --> 00:04:26,540
I brought him here.

7
00:04:33,006 --> 00:04:36,331
You're too brave for a girl, Lukjan.

8
00:04:36,331 --> 00:04:39,860
You know the rules damn well,
and you disobeyed them.

9
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:47,478
My dad is a doctor and I am his daughter.

10
00:04:47,478 --> 00:04:52,000
You can't expect me
to leave an injured person by the roadside.

11
00:04:54,302 --> 00:04:56,563
That's it?

12
00:04:56,563 --> 00:04:59,406
Just for saving a stranger's life?

13
00:04:59,406 --> 00:05:03,310
You're risking your dad's
and your lives like this?

14
00:05:03,310 --> 00:05:05,111
What about your case?

15
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:10,440
When you first met my dad,

16
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:12,742
you didn't even know who he was.

17
00:05:12,742 --> 00:05:15,860
Still, you've spared his life until now.

18
00:05:16,662 --> 00:05:21,300
What's the difference between then and now?

19
00:05:33,115 --> 00:05:34,816
Who are you?

20
00:05:35,606 --> 00:05:37,254
I don't know.

21
00:05:37,254 --> 00:05:39,579
I don't remember anything.

22
00:05:39,579 --> 00:05:42,526
Hurry up and tell us who you are,
or you will be a dead man.

23
00:05:42,526 --> 00:05:44,808
I told you that I don't remember anything.

24
00:05:44,808 --> 00:05:46,435
Stop it. That's enough!

25
00:05:46,435 --> 00:05:50,515
I have a reason for saving his life.

26
00:05:50,515 --> 00:05:53,340
Tell me the reason.

27
00:05:59,792 --> 00:06:01,580
I'm suspecting...

28
00:06:03,227 --> 00:06:06,528
that this guy is Tawan, the Bandit.

29
00:06:19,422 --> 00:06:24,187
Tawan, the Bandit has gone missing
for two years

30
00:06:24,187 --> 00:06:27,020
after he robbed a millionaire's house
in the city.

31
00:06:29,179 --> 00:06:30,980
Tawan...

32
00:06:32,432 --> 00:06:34,384
is a legend.

33
00:06:34,384 --> 00:06:38,555
He is a heroic bandit
that the officers are searching for.

34
00:06:38,555 --> 00:06:45,620
<i>Nobody has ever seen
what he really looks like.</i>

35
00:06:47,395 --> 00:06:49,600
<i>This man is Tawan, the Bandit</i>

36
00:06:50,254 --> 00:06:54,540
who would rob the rich to feed the poor.

37
00:06:56,923 --> 00:06:58,624
Isn't it right?

38
00:06:58,624 --> 00:07:02,018
Do you think what I said was right?

39
00:07:05,064 --> 00:07:06,765
That's right.

40
00:07:07,726 --> 00:07:10,428
I think this man could be Tawan.

41
00:07:10,428 --> 00:07:17,379
But he is injured, so he lost his memories.

42
00:07:17,379 --> 00:07:20,078
And he can't remember who he is.

43
00:07:20,078 --> 00:07:21,900
Don't believe them.

44
00:07:22,632 --> 00:07:25,500
Her words are contradictory.

45
00:07:26,363 --> 00:07:30,579
You said that nobody
has ever seen Tawan's face,

46
00:07:30,579 --> 00:07:33,660
then how do you know
that he really is Tawan?

47
00:07:36,808 --> 00:07:39,864
What should he do so you could trust him?

48
00:07:39,864 --> 00:07:41,565
Hey.

49
00:08:02,736 --> 00:08:05,704
If he really is Tawan, the Bandit,

50
00:08:05,704 --> 00:08:08,675
despite the fact that he lost his memories,

51
00:08:08,675 --> 00:08:12,260
his bandit's instinct still remains.

52
00:08:13,672 --> 00:08:15,940
If he isn't Tawan...

53
00:08:18,872 --> 00:08:21,150
I will personally chop off his head

54
00:08:21,150 --> 00:08:24,100
and hang it right in front of your place.

55
00:08:30,547 --> 00:08:32,300
Wait, Mai.

56
00:08:34,616 --> 00:08:37,180
Please let him recover for a bit.

57
00:08:38,670 --> 00:08:40,211
Mai,

58
00:08:40,963 --> 00:08:45,700
before proving anything,
can I test his skill just a little?

59
00:09:44,043 --> 00:09:45,744
What?

60
00:10:32,454 --> 00:10:34,155
Who told you to stop?

61
00:10:36,851 --> 00:10:38,552
Why don't you fight him?

62
00:12:12,520 --> 00:12:14,221
Do you think this is enough?

63
00:12:32,808 --> 00:12:36,456
I've seen enough crazy guys like you.

64
00:12:36,456 --> 00:12:41,200
To be the great bandit like me,
it requires something more.

65
00:12:50,924 --> 00:12:52,336
What are you doing?

66
00:12:52,336 --> 00:12:54,700
- Huh?
- Dad?

67
00:12:54,700 --> 00:12:55,755
Let me go.

68
00:12:55,755 --> 00:12:56,960
- Let me go.
- Let Lukjan go.

69
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:59,041
- Let me go!
- Lukjan...

70
00:13:00,760 --> 00:13:02,268
Let go of me!

71
00:13:03,048 --> 00:13:05,080
Stay still

72
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:07,060
if you wish to stay alive...

73
00:13:42,912 --> 00:13:45,542
I will give you a chance to prove yourself.

74
00:13:45,542 --> 00:13:48,774
I will give you one bullet.

75
00:13:48,774 --> 00:13:51,800
If you miss it, Lukjan will die.

76
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:54,854
If you hit the target,

77
00:13:54,854 --> 00:13:57,740
I will accept you as Tawan, the Bandit.

78
00:15:11,286 --> 00:15:12,987
Lukjan?

79
00:15:42,483 --> 00:15:44,184
Lukjan?

80
00:15:45,054 --> 00:15:47,182
Are you okay?

81
00:15:47,182 --> 00:15:48,940
I'm fine, Dad.

82
00:16:10,763 --> 00:16:13,400
From now on, call me Tawan.

83
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:21,660
Anyone who wants to hurt
either Mr. Jit or Lukjan from now on...

84
00:16:24,131 --> 00:16:26,100
will face a death penalty from me.

85
00:17:28,107 --> 00:17:31,256
Did you get anything about Prince Rawi, Khet?

86
00:17:31,256 --> 00:17:33,022
Nothing.

87
00:17:33,022 --> 00:17:37,700
It's been two days,
and you still haven't found anything?

88
00:17:38,355 --> 00:17:42,780
It's basically a jungle in the area,
so it's hard to search for him.

89
00:17:43,552 --> 00:17:46,896
I don't care how hard
or struggling it is to find him,

90
00:17:46,896 --> 00:17:48,940
you have to find my son.

91
00:17:49,628 --> 00:17:51,629
I know it well,

92
00:17:51,629 --> 00:17:54,134
that's why I assigned officers
to search for him around the clock.

93
00:17:54,134 --> 00:17:56,380
Around the clock?

94
00:17:57,419 --> 00:18:00,060
And you found nothing?

95
00:18:02,040 --> 00:18:03,891
He is my one and only son.

96
00:18:03,891 --> 00:18:06,620
He needs to be fine, you hear me?

97
00:18:07,267 --> 00:18:08,968
Yes, ma'am.

98
00:18:10,432 --> 00:18:12,736
We are short-handed.

99
00:18:12,736 --> 00:18:15,136
We can search for him in a wider area.

100
00:18:15,136 --> 00:18:18,380
If you're understaffed,
then hire more people.

101
00:18:19,854 --> 00:18:21,374
I can pay for them.

102
00:18:21,374 --> 00:18:23,340
Even if we hire more people,

103
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:26,120
it's not that easy to find him.

104
00:18:26,120 --> 00:18:28,900
What did you say that?

105
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:31,280
What do you mean by that?

106
00:18:31,280 --> 00:18:34,940
Tell me, Khet. What are you hiding from me?

107
00:18:35,648 --> 00:18:37,600
Tell me!

108
00:18:37,600 --> 00:18:39,776
Just tell me.

109
00:18:39,776 --> 00:18:41,860
Like I said,

110
00:18:43,083 --> 00:18:47,480
he was lost in the jungle,
so it's hard to find him.

111
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:49,754
There are dangers everywhere,

112
00:18:49,754 --> 00:18:52,900
including bandits and venomous animals.

113
00:18:53,920 --> 00:18:55,891
Khet!

114
00:18:55,891 --> 00:18:57,940
What are you trying to tell me?

115
00:19:00,960 --> 00:19:02,580
Just tell me.

116
00:19:04,547 --> 00:19:06,248
I'm afraid that...

117
00:19:07,880 --> 00:19:10,500
Rawi won't make it out alive anymore.

118
00:19:19,587 --> 00:19:23,100
- Ma'am! Please have a seat.
- Sit down...

119
00:19:27,840 --> 00:19:30,020
He is my one and only son.

120
00:19:33,160 --> 00:19:35,140
He needs to be okay.

121
00:20:23,389 --> 00:20:25,788
What is wrong with you?

122
00:20:25,788 --> 00:20:27,725
You're acting as if I'm disgusting.

123
00:20:29,112 --> 00:20:30,813
I'm pregnant.

124
00:20:34,080 --> 00:20:36,660
And my husband knows about it.

125
00:20:37,766 --> 00:20:40,500
This baby will cause me my whole future.

126
00:20:41,179 --> 00:20:43,060
What should I do?

127
00:20:47,726 --> 00:20:49,427
Pring?

128
00:20:50,270 --> 00:20:52,101
Are you carrying my baby?

129
00:20:56,646 --> 00:20:58,460
I'm so happy...

130
00:20:59,168 --> 00:21:00,980
that this is our baby.

131
00:21:01,784 --> 00:21:04,340
I will protect you and the baby.

132
00:21:05,875 --> 00:21:07,900
I will make sure that our baby...

133
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:12,940
will become a descendant
of Wongnaruenart fully.

134
00:21:13,584 --> 00:21:19,120
After that,
our baby will gain the family's inheritance,

135
00:21:19,120 --> 00:21:20,821
all of it.

136
00:21:34,995 --> 00:21:37,400
I won't let you and the baby struggle.

137
00:21:47,662 --> 00:21:51,603
This is the place.
It is Prince Rawikan's office.

138
00:21:51,603 --> 00:21:54,088
Can I go inside?

139
00:21:54,088 --> 00:21:55,512
You can't.

140
00:21:55,512 --> 00:21:59,740
He was the only one
who can come in and out of the office.

141
00:22:14,632 --> 00:22:17,296
Ms. Ngamta, have I offended you?

142
00:22:17,296 --> 00:22:19,660
It seemed like you are giving me
the cold shoulder.

143
00:22:23,131 --> 00:22:26,518
That's right, I am angry with you.

144
00:22:26,518 --> 00:22:29,163
What did I do?

145
00:22:29,163 --> 00:22:31,595
You didn't know?

146
00:22:31,595 --> 00:22:33,920
What you told her about her son earlier.

147
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:36,930
You should have consoled her.

148
00:22:36,930 --> 00:22:40,259
Instead, you hurt her feelings
with your blunt words.

149
00:22:40,259 --> 00:22:43,380
How could you tell her
that her son was about to die?

150
00:22:44,032 --> 00:22:46,352
But it's the truth.

151
00:22:46,352 --> 00:22:48,038
I didn't want to lie to her.

152
00:22:48,038 --> 00:22:52,363
Right now, you should calm her down
and console her as much as you can.

153
00:22:52,363 --> 00:22:55,180
She is not feeling well right now.

154
00:23:00,030 --> 00:23:01,731
If that's the case,

155
00:23:02,824 --> 00:23:04,660
what should I say?

156
00:23:05,435 --> 00:23:06,662
Hey!

157
00:23:06,662 --> 00:23:08,934
If you can't come up with it by yourself,

158
00:23:08,934 --> 00:23:10,740
then you should be quiet.

159
00:23:36,155 --> 00:23:38,699
Tawan, you need some water?

160
00:23:38,699 --> 00:23:40,420
I can get it for you.

161
00:23:43,435 --> 00:23:45,704
Miang, you should go home.

162
00:23:45,704 --> 00:23:47,262
Come on, Uncle.

163
00:23:47,262 --> 00:23:50,179
Let me stay and help. Please? I want to help.

164
00:23:50,179 --> 00:23:53,272
Hey! What did I just say?

165
00:23:53,272 --> 00:23:57,880
Miang, you should go home. Trust me.

166
00:24:00,678 --> 00:24:02,379
Fine.

167
00:24:06,542 --> 00:24:08,740
Follow me to mix some medicines.

168
00:24:22,755 --> 00:24:24,456
Dad?

169
00:24:27,507 --> 00:24:31,283
As soon as his wounds are healed,
he needs to leave Prai Island.

170
00:24:31,283 --> 00:24:32,542
What?

171
00:24:32,542 --> 00:24:34,248
We talked about this.

172
00:24:34,248 --> 00:24:36,958
We will help him
until he gets back his memory.

173
00:24:36,958 --> 00:24:39,507
That was before he met Mai.

174
00:24:39,507 --> 00:24:41,774
I don't trust him.

175
00:24:41,774 --> 00:24:46,040
I saw how he fought with Mai's guys.

176
00:24:46,040 --> 00:24:47,819
And I didn't feel good about it.

177
00:24:47,819 --> 00:24:50,260
I'm worried that
he could be an actual bandit.

178
00:24:51,062 --> 00:24:52,886
Aren't you too pessimistic?

179
00:24:52,886 --> 00:24:54,592
Pessimistic about what?

180
00:24:54,592 --> 00:24:56,760
I am speaking the truth.

181
00:24:56,760 --> 00:24:59,540
You know it well
that he wasn't just a regular villager.

182
00:25:00,339 --> 00:25:02,168
Look at his skin.

183
00:25:02,168 --> 00:25:05,704
Look at how he dressed in expensive clothes
when you first met him.

184
00:25:05,704 --> 00:25:11,180
I think he could lie to us
that he lost his memory.

185
00:25:16,766 --> 00:25:18,478
See?

186
00:25:18,478 --> 00:25:20,700
You are starting
to have a second thoughts, aren't you?

187
00:25:23,784 --> 00:25:26,334
You need to take a good care of him.

188
00:25:26,334 --> 00:25:29,854
If his condition is getting worse,
he will stay here longer.

189
00:25:29,854 --> 00:25:33,220
We need to heal him fast so he can leave.

190
00:25:58,483 --> 00:26:01,502
Did you really believe
that he is Tawan, the Bandit?

191
00:26:01,502 --> 00:26:03,580
What did you expect me to do?

192
00:26:04,339 --> 00:26:07,230
Didn't you see him with your own eyes?

193
00:26:07,230 --> 00:26:10,520
He completed all of my tasks.

194
00:26:10,520 --> 00:26:11,630
That's right.

195
00:26:11,630 --> 00:26:14,360
He completed his tasks.

196
00:26:14,360 --> 00:26:16,678
But are you going to let him
walk around like this?

197
00:26:16,678 --> 00:26:19,320
I think we should just kill him.

198
00:26:19,320 --> 00:26:20,700
We can't!

199
00:26:21,680 --> 00:26:25,808
I keep my promises,
and I am a man of my word.

200
00:26:25,808 --> 00:26:30,640
I told Jit that I would spare his life,
and I need to follow it.

201
00:26:30,640 --> 00:26:33,660
Besides, I see that we can benefit from him.

202
00:26:34,368 --> 00:26:36,363
Benefit us, how?

203
00:26:36,363 --> 00:26:40,563
It is rare to find someone like Tawan.

204
00:26:40,563 --> 00:26:45,822
He is talented, intelligent,
and willing to take risks.

205
00:26:45,822 --> 00:26:50,059
It should be better to have him on our side,

206
00:26:50,059 --> 00:26:53,760
because he should know better ways of robbery

207
00:26:53,760 --> 00:26:56,000
which can go beyond this area.

208
00:27:04,254 --> 00:27:05,950
Fai?

209
00:27:05,950 --> 00:27:07,960
Why did Mai say something like that?

210
00:27:07,960 --> 00:27:10,056
It was like he was taking that guy's side.

211
00:27:10,056 --> 00:27:12,462
Are you going to follow his orders?

212
00:27:12,462 --> 00:27:14,163
No way.

213
00:27:16,972 --> 00:27:18,780
I don't trust him.

214
00:27:19,710 --> 00:27:24,160
My gut is telling me that
he will bring trouble to us.

215
00:27:51,067 --> 00:27:52,768
What are you looking at?

216
00:27:53,462 --> 00:27:55,163
I'm not looking.

217
00:28:05,467 --> 00:28:08,580
To heal your internal bruises,
you need to take it all.

218
00:28:12,160 --> 00:28:13,980
So you will recover.

219
00:28:53,550 --> 00:28:55,255
Hey!

220
00:28:57,971 --> 00:28:59,278
Why are you tying me up?

221
00:28:59,278 --> 00:29:00,766
Stop!

222
00:29:00,766 --> 00:29:02,488
Don't move!

223
00:29:02,488 --> 00:29:03,507
Let me go!

224
00:29:03,507 --> 00:29:05,040
I'm not letting you go!

225
00:29:05,040 --> 00:29:06,680
I will let you go

226
00:29:06,680 --> 00:29:10,370
when you answer
all of my questions truthfully.

227
00:29:10,370 --> 00:29:12,170
Answer me!

228
00:29:12,170 --> 00:29:13,871
Who are you?

229
00:29:15,219 --> 00:29:17,880
I've told you already
that I don't remember anything.

230
00:29:17,880 --> 00:29:19,454
I don't believe you.

231
00:29:19,454 --> 00:29:21,256
You don't remember anything,

232
00:29:21,256 --> 00:29:24,420
but why can you fight?
How did you know how to use a gun?

233
00:29:25,355 --> 00:29:29,600
You can fool everyone here,
but you can't fool me.

234
00:29:29,600 --> 00:29:32,000
If you refuse to say the truth...

235
00:29:34,368 --> 00:29:36,280
Hey!

236
00:29:36,280 --> 00:29:38,176
Tell me who you are.

237
00:29:38,176 --> 00:29:40,200
You need to calm down.

238
00:29:40,200 --> 00:29:45,020
Well, that depends on your answer
whether it can calm me down.

239
00:29:46,563 --> 00:29:48,500
I told you, all of it.

240
00:29:50,750 --> 00:29:52,820
Where did you get this ring from?

241
00:29:54,630 --> 00:29:55,947
Tell me the truth.

242
00:29:55,947 --> 00:29:59,084
Where did you get the ring? Tell me!

243
00:30:09,334 --> 00:30:10,880
Let me go!

244
00:30:10,880 --> 00:30:12,624
I knew that you can't be trusted.

245
00:30:12,624 --> 00:30:16,020
- You son of a bitch! Let me go!
- Hey! Stop!

246
00:30:17,400 --> 00:30:18,910
I'm not letting you go.

247
00:30:18,910 --> 00:30:21,384
If I let you go, you will try to kill me.

248
00:30:21,384 --> 00:30:24,020
I'm not a cruel person like you.

249
00:30:24,720 --> 00:30:26,651
You killed him, didn't you?

250
00:30:26,651 --> 00:30:29,000
You killed the owner of this ring,
didn't you?

251
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:31,595
Hey! Get a grip!

252
00:30:31,595 --> 00:30:33,580
I didn't kill anybody.

253
00:30:34,720 --> 00:30:36,894
I don't know where I got this ring from.

254
00:30:36,894 --> 00:30:39,060
I told you that I don't remember.

255
00:30:40,142 --> 00:30:41,603
Hey!

256
00:30:41,603 --> 00:30:43,620
I think we need to talk nicely.

257
00:31:01,875 --> 00:31:03,619
I don't believe you.

258
00:31:03,619 --> 00:31:04,976
Tell me the truth.

259
00:31:04,976 --> 00:31:07,803
- Tell me!
- This is the truth!

260
00:31:07,803 --> 00:31:09,899
I can tell you the same thing
for the hundredth time,

261
00:31:09,899 --> 00:31:11,680
because it is the truth.

262
00:31:11,680 --> 00:31:14,240
I don't even know who I am.

263
00:31:14,240 --> 00:31:16,860
I don't know where I got this ring from.

264
00:31:17,595 --> 00:31:20,380
What you expect me to do?
I don't know anything!

265
00:31:21,126 --> 00:31:23,337
And you told everyone
that I was Tawan, the Bandit.

266
00:31:23,337 --> 00:31:25,180
I didn't say it.

267
00:31:28,419 --> 00:31:30,675
About all the tricks
that Mai told me to perform,

268
00:31:30,675 --> 00:31:34,220
I did them all,
and I didn't even know how I did them.

269
00:31:43,758 --> 00:31:45,459
I really have no idea.

270
00:31:46,120 --> 00:31:48,300
I have no idea how I could do them.

271
00:31:49,016 --> 00:31:51,507
When I showed him the tricks,

272
00:31:51,507 --> 00:31:54,300
I saw something in my head.

273
00:31:56,211 --> 00:32:01,940
It popped up shortly
and I didn't know what it was.

274
00:32:03,635 --> 00:32:08,420
Believe me, Lukjan,
when I said that I have amnesia.

275
00:32:09,966 --> 00:32:11,667
It's the truth.

276
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:24,701
Fine.

277
00:32:26,678 --> 00:32:28,379
I believe you.

278
00:32:30,240 --> 00:32:34,694
But if I find out that you lied to me,
I will kill you.

279
00:33:04,976 --> 00:33:06,677
Tiew.

280
00:33:12,715 --> 00:33:14,416
I love you.

281
00:33:22,646 --> 00:33:24,420
What did you say?

282
00:33:26,297 --> 00:33:28,300
Say it again?

283
00:33:30,830 --> 00:33:32,531
I love you.

284
00:33:40,139 --> 00:33:42,740
I love you, too.

285
00:33:54,195 --> 00:33:55,280
Sir?

286
00:33:55,280 --> 00:33:58,760
We've been searching for clues for days,
and we got nothing.

287
00:33:58,760 --> 00:34:01,160
I think that prince

288
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:03,920
could have been eaten up by tigers,
and there were only his bones left.

289
00:34:03,920 --> 00:34:06,140
It'd be better if he died.

290
00:34:07,614 --> 00:34:09,540
I'm afraid that...

291
00:34:11,256 --> 00:34:13,500
he could still be alive.

292
00:34:27,171 --> 00:34:28,872
Hello.

293
00:35:01,040 --> 00:35:03,564
Why did you call me here all of a sudden?

294
00:35:03,564 --> 00:35:05,880
What do you think? There is only one thing.

295
00:35:05,880 --> 00:35:07,730
My heart is burning up, I can't sleep or eat.

296
00:35:07,730 --> 00:35:09,430
I'm about to burst now.

297
00:35:09,430 --> 00:35:11,214
Do you know that Officer Khetdan,

298
00:35:11,214 --> 00:35:14,912
my husband's best friend,
is searching for him?

299
00:35:14,912 --> 00:35:17,200
Officer Khetdan?

300
00:35:17,200 --> 00:35:18,875
I know him.

301
00:35:18,875 --> 00:35:21,171
He is working under me.

302
00:35:21,171 --> 00:35:23,304
Then you have to do something.

303
00:35:23,304 --> 00:35:25,517
If he finds him before us,

304
00:35:25,517 --> 00:35:28,990
we both will be dead for sure.

305
00:35:28,990 --> 00:35:31,424
Even if that officer found him first,

306
00:35:31,424 --> 00:35:33,280
your husband never saw my face.

307
00:35:33,280 --> 00:35:35,860
He wouldn't know that I did it.

308
00:35:37,910 --> 00:35:40,600
You don't know Prince Rawikan well enough.

309
00:35:40,600 --> 00:35:42,238
He's smart.

310
00:35:42,238 --> 00:35:46,093
He will connect the dots in no time.

311
00:35:46,093 --> 00:35:49,187
That's when we both will be in real trouble.

312
00:35:49,187 --> 00:35:51,980
Hey! You don't have to overthink it.

313
00:35:53,491 --> 00:35:55,864
How could you say that?

314
00:35:55,864 --> 00:35:59,850
I ordered you to kill him,
you made a mistake and he fled.

315
00:35:59,850 --> 00:36:02,000
Now everything ended up like this.

316
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:05,827
You need to do something to stop this.

317
00:36:05,827 --> 00:36:09,182
That prince was dead for sure.

318
00:36:09,182 --> 00:36:11,760
I just haven't found his body yet.

319
00:36:11,760 --> 00:36:15,381
As for Officer Khetdan,
I will take care of it.

320
00:36:16,080 --> 00:36:17,781
Don't make another mistake.

321
00:36:46,344 --> 00:36:48,045
Pring, honey.

322
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:55,340
You must still be in shock
about what happened to your husband.

323
00:37:02,224 --> 00:37:05,040
Don't dwell on it too much.

324
00:37:05,040 --> 00:37:08,280
You need to think of your baby
before doing anything.

325
00:37:08,280 --> 00:37:10,752
You can't let anything happen to it.

326
00:37:10,752 --> 00:37:13,800
If something bad really happens
to your husband,

327
00:37:16,016 --> 00:37:20,904
the baby will be our survival ticket.

328
00:37:35,453 --> 00:37:37,060
Why are you laughing?

329
00:37:38,350 --> 00:37:41,300
Your husband has gone missing
and you're still laughing?

330
00:37:43,480 --> 00:37:45,860
My husband has gone missing...

331
00:37:47,667 --> 00:37:49,820
because of me.

332
00:38:04,339 --> 00:38:06,360
You stupid bitch!

333
00:38:06,360 --> 00:38:09,400
You keep on finding trouble for me. Why?

334
00:38:09,400 --> 00:38:10,814
Are you out of your mind?

335
00:38:10,814 --> 00:38:12,760
Why did you send someone
to kill your own husband?

336
00:38:12,760 --> 00:38:14,400
Mom! That hurts!

337
00:38:14,400 --> 00:38:16,320
Are you out of your freaking mind?

338
00:38:16,320 --> 00:38:17,920
Are you crazy?

339
00:38:17,920 --> 00:38:19,700
You need to stop.

340
00:38:20,435 --> 00:38:24,144
If you don't want to lose your treasure
from Naruenart Palace,

341
00:38:24,144 --> 00:38:27,515
you need to stay quiet and don't tell anyone.

342
00:38:27,515 --> 00:38:31,360
And you need to remember
that we are in the same boat.

343
00:38:31,360 --> 00:38:33,061
Don't tell a single soul.

344
00:38:36,350 --> 00:38:39,500
Do you want me to go crazy too?

345
00:38:42,104 --> 00:38:45,856
Well, we need to pray
that your husband is really dead.

346
00:38:45,856 --> 00:38:48,155
If he comes back,

347
00:38:48,155 --> 00:38:50,700
it's gonna be both of us who will be dead.

348
00:39:34,288 --> 00:39:35,419
Wake up!

349
00:39:35,419 --> 00:39:37,467
You can't stay in bed forever.

350
00:39:37,467 --> 00:39:38,974
Up!

351
00:39:40,069 --> 00:39:43,351
Wake up! Up!

352
00:39:45,400 --> 00:39:48,568
Get ready to work.
I will give you five minutes.

353
00:39:48,568 --> 00:39:50,840
One... Two...

354
00:39:50,840 --> 00:39:52,652
- Hey!
- Three... Four...

355
00:39:52,652 --> 00:39:55,500
Five... Six... Seven...

356
00:40:40,206 --> 00:40:44,030
What? You've been cleaning them for hours
and you're still not done?

357
00:40:44,030 --> 00:40:45,900
I'm still washing them.

358
00:40:47,725 --> 00:40:51,933
I think they are dirty and too rusty.

359
00:40:51,933 --> 00:40:53,688
I can't clean them completely.

360
00:40:53,688 --> 00:40:55,389
We should buy a new set.

361
00:40:56,595 --> 00:40:59,517
You think we have so much money?
This is Prai Island.

362
00:40:59,517 --> 00:41:01,820
We're lucky we have these to use.

363
00:41:09,771 --> 00:41:11,174
Why did you clean it like that?

364
00:41:11,174 --> 00:41:12,827
You have to do it like this, let me do it.

365
00:41:12,827 --> 00:41:15,008
You need to watch me.

366
00:41:15,008 --> 00:41:18,709
You need to scrub it, okay? Let's try.

367
00:41:27,822 --> 00:41:29,971
I don't think they'll be clean
if you keep doing this.

368
00:41:29,971 --> 00:41:31,039
They won't bite.

369
00:41:31,039 --> 00:41:33,790
Soak one and scrub it.

370
00:41:33,790 --> 00:41:36,385
Scrub! Scrub! Scrub!

371
00:41:36,385 --> 00:41:40,686
Just scrub it harder, it won't bite.

372
00:41:40,686 --> 00:41:42,387
Keep going.

373
00:41:52,160 --> 00:41:54,555
Chan's daughter will give birth tonight?

374
00:41:54,555 --> 00:41:57,566
That's right, I need to watch her closely.

375
00:41:57,566 --> 00:42:01,380
The baby is in the wrong position,
and it's dangerous.

376
00:42:03,560 --> 00:42:05,010
I don't know when she will give birth.

377
00:42:05,010 --> 00:42:06,950
I could be there until the next morning.

378
00:42:06,950 --> 00:42:08,651
Sure.

379
00:42:13,307 --> 00:42:16,539
I will ask Kratin
to keep you company tonight.

380
00:42:16,539 --> 00:42:17,640
No need to.

381
00:42:17,640 --> 00:42:19,107
What do you mean?

382
00:42:19,107 --> 00:42:21,491
I can't let you be here alone with Tawan.

383
00:42:21,491 --> 00:42:23,288
I don't trust him.

384
00:42:23,288 --> 00:42:26,125
This is the plan. I should get going.

385
00:42:26,125 --> 00:42:27,826
Got it.

386
00:42:39,061 --> 00:42:42,360
Hey! Where is Fai?

387
00:42:42,360 --> 00:42:44,670
You know when he is upset,

388
00:42:44,670 --> 00:42:48,643
he likes to go to the jungle
to hunt or shoot.

389
00:42:48,643 --> 00:42:50,277
He's furious about Tawan, isn't he?

390
00:42:50,277 --> 00:42:51,683
Look at that guy.

391
00:42:51,683 --> 00:42:54,344
It is likely that he will replace Fai
as Mai's favorite guy.

392
00:42:54,344 --> 00:42:57,102
Hey! Stop saying that.

393
00:42:57,102 --> 00:42:59,278
I am Fai's man, and I won't let that happen.

394
00:42:59,278 --> 00:43:01,219
And what are you going to do with that?

395
00:43:01,219 --> 00:43:02,920
Right.

396
00:43:03,608 --> 00:43:06,260
He needs to know his place here.

397
00:43:28,727 --> 00:43:30,700
Mai can stop me from messing with you...

398
00:43:36,211 --> 00:43:38,860
but you can magically disappear.

399
00:43:46,675 --> 00:43:50,235
Am I doing the right thing
by letting Tawan go by himself?

400
00:43:50,235 --> 00:43:51,936
I shouldn't.

401
00:43:59,232 --> 00:44:01,460
What if he gets lost?

402
00:44:18,622 --> 00:44:21,580
Fai has gone missing?

403
00:44:22,246 --> 00:44:25,072
That's right. But it is not only Fai,

404
00:44:25,072 --> 00:44:28,800
Tawan and Lukjan have gone missing too.

405
00:44:28,800 --> 00:44:33,900
I think Tawan and Lukjan are holding Fai
as their hostage.

406
00:44:39,198 --> 00:44:41,899
Why would they do that?

407
00:44:41,899 --> 00:44:45,317
I have no idea. Right, guys?

408
00:44:57,451 --> 00:45:01,915
You think you can lie to my face?

409
00:45:01,915 --> 00:45:04,107
I'm not lying to you.

410
00:45:04,107 --> 00:45:05,957
I'm only speaking the truth.

411
00:45:05,957 --> 00:45:08,382
I'll give you another chance.

412
00:45:12,320 --> 00:45:14,500
Fine, this is the truth.

413
00:47:08,774 --> 00:47:11,060
You forced me into this.

414
00:47:28,958 --> 00:47:33,500
After I kill you, I will kill Lukjan next.

415
00:48:15,198 --> 00:48:17,619
Tawan! Tawan!

416
00:48:17,619 --> 00:48:20,547
That's enough! Tawan, let him go.

417
00:48:20,547 --> 00:48:22,560
Let him go.

418
00:48:22,560 --> 00:48:24,592
Stop it! Let him go.

419
00:48:24,592 --> 00:48:26,950
Tawan! Stop it!

420
00:48:26,950 --> 00:48:28,120
That's enough.

421
00:48:28,120 --> 00:48:31,062
I know that you're a good guy,
and you're nothing like them bandits.

422
00:48:31,062 --> 00:48:34,816
But if you kill him now,
you are no better than him.

423
00:48:34,816 --> 00:48:36,820
Tawan!

424
00:48:50,307 --> 00:48:52,611
You get cocky when I was so nice to you?

425
00:48:52,611 --> 00:48:55,176
And you're hurting one of my guys?

426
00:48:55,176 --> 00:48:57,054
Well, your guy tried to kill me first.

427
00:48:57,054 --> 00:48:58,424
I'm just defending myself.

428
00:48:58,424 --> 00:48:59,534
Not true, he is lying.

429
00:48:59,534 --> 00:49:00,830
I am not lying.

430
00:49:00,830 --> 00:49:02,063
You tried to kill me first.

431
00:49:02,063 --> 00:49:03,549
No, you tried to kill me.

432
00:49:03,549 --> 00:49:05,250
It's you.

433
00:49:09,000 --> 00:49:11,860
If you said that you didn't start it,
will you swear?

434
00:49:19,171 --> 00:49:20,980
What do you say?

435
00:49:21,926 --> 00:49:25,072
I... I mean...

436
00:49:25,072 --> 00:49:28,230
This is obvious
that Tawan is telling the truth.

437
00:49:28,230 --> 00:49:30,700
- Lukjan!
- That's enough!

438
00:49:32,816 --> 00:49:34,902
You're fighting like animals.

439
00:49:34,902 --> 00:49:39,260
Don't let me see these nonsense fights again.

440
00:49:42,699 --> 00:49:44,980
Fai, we should go.

441
00:50:11,904 --> 00:50:13,574
I can't stay here anymore.

442
00:50:13,574 --> 00:50:15,942
I need to go and find my son.

443
00:50:15,942 --> 00:50:17,744
I can't just sit still and do nothing.

444
00:50:17,744 --> 00:50:19,798
I will find my son by myself.

445
00:50:19,798 --> 00:50:21,540
But ma'am...

446
00:50:22,725 --> 00:50:25,600
Where are you going to find him?

447
00:50:25,600 --> 00:50:28,523
I don't know but I have to go.

448
00:50:28,523 --> 00:50:31,584
I can't sit still in the palace
and do nothing.

449
00:50:31,584 --> 00:50:34,240
- I need to go.
- You can't.

450
00:50:34,240 --> 00:50:36,054
You can't go anywhere.

451
00:50:36,054 --> 00:50:38,894
Mr. Khetdan told you to wait for news here.

452
00:50:38,894 --> 00:50:40,339
Who are you to tell me what to do?

453
00:50:40,339 --> 00:50:42,734
I need to find my son.

454
00:50:42,734 --> 00:50:44,968
Please don't go.

455
00:50:44,968 --> 00:50:46,195
I need to go.

456
00:50:46,195 --> 00:50:47,203
Ma'am.

457
00:50:47,203 --> 00:50:49,880
- You can't stop me.
- You can't go anywhere.

458
00:50:49,880 --> 00:50:52,900
I will go find him, no matter what. Move!

459
00:50:53,592 --> 00:50:55,293
Ma'am?

460
00:50:56,152 --> 00:50:57,758
What is happening?

461
00:50:57,758 --> 00:50:59,980
We will find out soon.

462
00:51:02,830 --> 00:51:05,208
- Ma'am, please don't go.
- Auntie?

463
00:51:05,208 --> 00:51:06,360
- Auntie?
- Ma'am...

464
00:51:06,360 --> 00:51:09,420
- Auntie?
- Please listen to me.

465
00:51:11,590 --> 00:51:13,786
You can't go out at night, ma'am.

466
00:51:14,734 --> 00:51:16,520
Who are you?

467
00:51:16,520 --> 00:51:19,540
This is Deputy Mesa. He is my boss.
